CSS Course Syllabus

Module 1: Introduction to CSS
1.1 - Introduction to CSS: What is CSS, Importance of CSS, Types of CSS (Inline, Internal, External)
1.2 - CSS Syntax: Selectors, Properties, and Values
1.3 - Applying CSS to HTML: Linking CSS to HTML files (External, Internal, Inline)
1.4 - CSS Selectors: Simple selectors (element, class, id), Attribute selectors, Grouping selectors, Pseudo-class selectors, Pseudo-element selectors

Module 2: CSS Box Model
2.1 - Understanding the CSS Box Model: Margin, Border, Padding, and Content
2.2 - Box Sizing: Content-box vs Border-box
2.3 - Width and Height properties
2.4 - Margin and Padding properties
2.5 - Borders: Border styles, Border radius
2.6 - Outline vs Border

Module 3: CSS Layouts and Positioning
3.1 - CSS Display Property: Block, Inline, Inline-block
3.2 - CSS Positioning: Static, Relative, Absolute, Fixed, Sticky
3.3 - Float and Clear
3.4 - Flexbox Layout: Understanding Flexbox, Main Axis, Cross Axis, Flex container properties, Flex item properties
3.5 - Grid Layout: CSS Grid vs Flexbox, Grid properties, Creating grid layouts
3.6 - Centering elements using CSS (vertically and horizontally)

Module 4: CSS Typography
4.1 - Fonts and Text: Font-family, Font-size, Font-weight, Line-height
4.2 - Text Styling: Text-transform, Text-decoration, Letter-spacing, Word-spacing
4.3 - Color: Color property, Background color, RGBA, Opacity
4.4 - CSS Variables (Custom Properties): Defining and using custom CSS variables
4.5 - Units in CSS: Pixels, Em, Rem, Percentages

Module 5: Advanced CSS Concepts
5.1 - CSS Transitions: Transition properties, Timing functions
5.2 - CSS Animations: Keyframes, Animation properties
5.3 - CSS Transformations: Rotate, Scale, Translate, Skew
5.4 - Responsive Design: Media Queries, Mobile-first design, Viewport units (vw, vh)
5.5 - CSS Frameworks: Introduction to Bootstrap, Foundation, Bulma

Module 6: CSS Best Practices and Optimization
6.1 - Writing Maintainable CSS: Naming conventions (BEM, OOCSS)
6.2 - CSS Preprocessors: Introduction to SASS and LESS
6.3 - Debugging CSS: Common issues and how to fix them
6.4 - Performance Optimization: Minification, Compression, Avoiding reflows and repaints

Module 7: CSS Project
7.1 - Build a responsive website using HTML and CSS
7.2 - Implement a layout using Flexbox or Grid
7.3 - Add interactivity using transitions and animations
7.4 - Optimize CSS for performance
